children.subject: It varies a lot based on the company you're interview with. For the large part, companies will ask about basic algorithms and data structures, but I know Twitch asks stuff about memory management, and Databricks straight up asks about JVM optimization.

With regard to 61C depends on the company and the role. e.g. software at a startup vs. QA at Intel -- the latter will probably require more knowledge of 61C stuff.

You will be able to tell by analyzing job descriptions...hopefully!
